hui
Homonym Number:  1
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a Maori community gathering, meeting, or social occasion
Origin: Maori
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: [Ma. <b>hui (-a)</b> gather, meeting] cf. P.M. Ryan Dict. Modern Maori (1995) 60. [W3 1. Hawaii 2. Hawaian & Maori: community gathering: Assembly [quot NZJAg].]
